# Performance

## Database

- Paginate all lists; cap `limit`
- Use `select` over deep `include`
- Avoid N+1 queries
- Use `$transaction` batch instead of sequential awaits when related

## Parallelism

```typescript
// ✅ Independent queries
const [items, total] = await prisma.$transaction([
  prisma.user.findMany({ where, skip, take }),
  prisma.user.count({ where }),
]);

// ✅ Independent unrelated calls
await Promise.all([sendEmail(), updateCache()]);
```

## Avoid

- Duplicate identical Prisma calls in one request
- Unnecessary JSON serialization round-trips
- Sync blocking on hot paths

## HTTP

- `compression()` enabled globally
- Keep response payloads minimal — DTO/select fields only

## Caching

Do not add Redis/in-memory cache unless explicitly requested. See `caching.mdc` when introduced.

## Measure first

Do not optimize prematurely. Add indexes for proven slow queries.
